definitions.definition: The terminal point of something in space or time.
examples: At the end of the garden there was a beautiful fountain.
At the end of the story, the main characters fall in love.

definitions.definition: The cessation of an effort, activity, state, or motion.
examples: Is there no end to this madness?
He met a terrible end in the jungle.
I hope the end comes quickly.

definitions.definition: The most extreme point of an object, especially one that is longer than it is wide.
examples: Hold the string at both ends .
My father always sat at the end of the table nearest the kitchen.
For what end should I toil?
The end of our club is to advance conversation and friendship.

definitions.definition: One of the two parts of the ground used as a descriptive name for half of the ground.
The position at the end of either the offensive or defensive line , a tight end , a split end , a defensive end .
A period of play in which each team throws eight rocks, two per player, in alternating fashion.
An ideal point of a graph or other complex . See End (graph theory)
That which is left; a remnant; a fragment; a scrap.
One of the yarns of the worsted warp in a Brussels carpet .

examples: Don't give them your ends . You jack that shit!
